This paper discusses a methodology for investigating the BitTorrent Sync protocol, which is used for data synchronization and replication. The paper focuses on security concerns and the control of data flow across security perimeters, which suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
